http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Two-city-youths-drown-in-Chennai/article13997909.ece

Two engineering students from Bengaluru drowned in the Bay of Bengal in Chennai on Monday.The duo have been identified as Joshva Akash and Suman H.S., students of Siddaganga Institute of Technology, Tumakuru.College principal Dr. Shivakumaraiah said that the two sixth semester students, studying architecture, had gone on a study tour to Chennai and Mahabalipuram in Tamilnadu.He said that the two were caught in a high tide and drowned. The bodies of the two students were recovered and handed over to the parents. The students had left Tumakuru on Saturday evening.